              ...&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;/m:addresses&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;/m:person-with-address&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              2) I notice that person.xsd is extensible and so I create
              my own compliant &lt;br&gt;
              person.xsd documents like so&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;p:person ...&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              ...&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;m:addresses&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;a:address ...&gt;...&lt;/a:address&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              ...&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;/m:addresses&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;/p:person&gt;&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              3) Suppose I take approach #2 and yourfriends.example.com
              notices and decides to &lt;br&gt;
              host them. They wish to offer both representations (their
              original and my &lt;br&gt;
